      "inheritance_hierarchy": "EdgeChallengeManager inherits Initializable and implements IEdgeChallengeManager; uses EdgeChallengeManagerLib and ChallengeEdgeLib for storage/memory edge operations. RollupUserLogic inherits RollupCore, UUPSNotUpgradeable, and implements IRollupUser. RollupCore inherits PausableUpgradeable and implements IRollupCore (and thus IAssertionChain interface methods). Libraries: RollupLib, AssertionNodeLib, AssertionStateLib, MerkleTreeLib, UintUtilsLib, ArrayUtilsLib, EdgeChallengeManagerLib, ChallengeEdgeLib. External protocol dependencies via interfaces: IBridge, IOutbox, IInboxBase, ISequencerInbox, IOneStepProofEntry.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin: Initializable (upgradeable initializer pattern)",
        "OpenZeppelin: PausableUpgradeable (pause state + whenNotPaused modifier)",
        "OpenZeppelin: SafeERC20 (used for stake token transfers)",
        "External interface: IOneStepProofEntry (one-step proof execution + machine hash)",
        "External interface: IBridge (sequencerMessageCount, sequencerInboxAccs, sequencerInbox address)",
        "External interface: IOutbox (updateSendRoot)",
        "External interface: ISequencerInbox (batch posting/force inclusion/admin setters; not implemented here)",
        "Arbitrum-specific: ArbSys precompile usage in RollupCore (only if running on Arbitrum chain)"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "EdgeChallengeManager is upgradeable via OZ Initializable (no explicit proxy implementation shown, but constructor disables initializers implying proxy deployment). RollupUserLogic is intended to be used behind a proxy (has onlyProxy modifier usage via UUPSNotUpgradeable) but is itself marked NotUpgradeable (UUPSNotUpgradeable suggests proxy admin pattern with restricted upgrades; exact upgrade mechanism not included in provided files). No Diamond pattern detected in provided code.",
      "access_control_structure": "RollupUserLogic uses onlyValidator modifier (isValidator[msg.sender] || validatorWhitelistDisabled) and Pausable whenNotPaused. anyTrustFastConfirmer is a single-address privileged confirmer. Rollup owner/admin is exposed via owner() returning _getAdmin() (proxy admin). EdgeChallengeManager enforces validator gating only in createLayerZeroEdge when assertionChain whitelist is enabled; most other EdgeChallengeManager functions are permissionless (anyone can bisect/confirm/update timers/refund if conditions met). Sequencer/batch poster controls live in external ISequencerInbox (not analyzed implementation)."
    },
